name: spavro
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "spavro" %}
{% set version = "1.1.24" %}


package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 82d0b436465bffc50d8b3f800b70ae01c67f75a92ba1abc7c395ae506c4901b7

build:
  number: 3
  script:
    - rm src/spavro/fast_binary.c     # [unix]
    - del src\\spavro\\fast_binary.c  # [win]
    - {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}
  host:
    - cython
    - pip
    - python
  run:
    - python
    - six >=1.10.0

test:
  imports:
    - spavro
  commands:
    - pip check
  requires:
    - pip

about:
  home: http://github.com/pluralsight/spavro
  summary: An Avro library, Spavro is a (sp)eedier avro implementation using Cython -- Spavro is a fork of the official Apache AVRO python 2 implementation with the goal of greatly improving data read deserialization and write serialization performance.
  license: Apache-2.0
  license_file: LICENSE.txt

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - mariusvniekerk
